narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: TAKE THIS CLASS. Griffel's amazing and you'll learn more than most other classes.
A lot of reading, but if you're interested in religious history, it's perfect for you.

I would not really recommend Modern Middle East Studies 292 01 to a fellow student, unless they're super interested in the subject material. Even then, the course has the unfortunate tendency of going too broadly and not deeply into the material it explores.
I would recommend this course to anyone interested in the recent history of islam. this course is good as a follow up to professor Griffel's lecture course on Jihad and Fundamentalism.
This was a great course! I highly recommend it.
